<item>
            <title>[SEC-996] AccessDeniedhandlerimpl  doesn&apos;t write response code if used with errorPage</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-996</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The forward to the error page will cause the response to be committed and thus the 403 error code cannot be written (the commit check was introduced as a fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-324&quot; title=&quot;AccessDeniedHandlerImpl always throws IllegalStateException&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-324&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-324&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), but the code should perhaps be written before the forward instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="24137">SEC-996</key>
            <summary>AccessDeniedhandlerimpl  doesn&apos;t write response code if used with errorPage</summary>
